  "prompt": "What kind of clothes should I wear for a home date?",
  "response": "For a home date, comfort and personal style are key. Here are some suggestions:\n\n1. Casual and comfortable options:\n- Soft, well-fitted jeans or leggings\n- Comfortable sweater or cozy top\n- Relaxed button-up shirt\n- Comfortable dress or loungewear\n\n2. Consider the activity:\n- Cooking together: Wear something you don't mind getting slightly messy\n- Movie night: Wear layers you can adjust for temperature\n- Game night: Wear something that allows easy movement\n\n3. Style tips:\n- Look put-together but not overdressed\n- Choose something that makes you feel confident\n- Opt for soft, comfortable fabrics\n- Avoid anything too restricting\n\n4. General advice:\n- Make sure your outfit reflects your personal style\n- Consider your partner's preferences\n- Ensure you feel comfortable and confident\n\nRemember, the most important thing is to be yourself and feel at ease.",
